<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="490" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,941,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,978,1004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,451,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Protearomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="greciana">
<emphasis box="[325,451,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">P. greciana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most common in Mediterranean areas and less so further north, although recently the species has been recorded several times in the 
<collectingCountry box="[681,785,1014,1040]" name="Germany" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Germany</collectingCountry>
states of 
<collectingRegion box="[896,986,1014,1040]" country="Germany" name="Bayern" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Bavaria</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[998,1065,1014,1040]" country="Germany" name="Hessen" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Hesse</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1121,1206,1014,1040]" country="Germany" name="Sachsen" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Saxony</collectingRegion>
, (unpublished data). Habitat preferences are not clearly understood but 
<bibRefCitation author="McAlpine, J. F." box="[725,921,1050,1076]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" pagination="885 - 903" refId="ref4727" refString="McAlpine, J. F. (1983) A revision of the genus Protearomyia McAlpine (Diptera, Lonchaeidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 115 (8), 885 - 903. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 115885 - 8" type="journal article" year="1983">McAlpine (1983)</bibRefCitation>
mentions that the 
<typeStatus box="[1132,1180,1050,1076]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">type</typeStatus>
material was captured in an oak forest in 
<collectingCountry box="[371,454,1086,1112]" name="Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Greece</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="MacGowan, I. &amp; Freidberg, A." box="[466,829,1086,1112]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" pagination="61 - 92" refId="ref4480" refString="MacGowan, I. &amp; Freidberg, A. (2008) The Lonchaeidae (Diptera) of Israel, with descriptions of three new species. Israel Journal of Entomology, 38, 61 - 92." type="journal article" year="2008">MacGowan &amp; Freidberg (2008)</bibRefCitation>
also list a specimen as being captured on oak and at altitudes of up to 
<quantity box="[353,439,1122,1148]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[477,543,1122,1148]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Israel</collectingCountry>
. Most of the German specimens were found in dry pine-beech forests or more moist areas with many poplar trees, but there are also records from dry grasslands. Localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1256,1436,1158,1184]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
include forest-steppe with oak forest; forest-steppe; damp meadow and edge of lowland wood near a pond (
<bibRefCitation author="Maca, J. &amp; Kubik S. &amp; Bartak, M." pageId="3" pageNumber="490" pagination="246 - 250" refId="ref4240" refString="Maca, J., Kubik S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2005) Lonchaeidae. In: Bartak, M. &amp; Kubik S. (Eds.), Diptera of Podyji National Park and its environs. Czech Agricultural University, Praha, pp. 246 - 250." type="book chapter" year="2005">
Máca 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">et al</emphasis>
. 2005
</bibRefCitation>
). Adults have been recorded between April and June.
</paragraph>
